title Pool P0 landed GREEN — the keystone host seam over Caravan's capability table
prompt Keaton said "proceed!" after the align pass named Pool P0 as the one aligned next build. Built it green rather than described it.
think studied Caravan first, as the align/finishing discipline requires -- read caravan/README.md and caravan/capabilities.rye. Found a real, bounded capability table (children, per-child capabilities, rights bitmask read/write/exec/net/device, and an allows(child,resource,right) query) already green. So Pool P0 composes on it rather than starting cold, exactly as the brief promised.
think made Caravan's capability query surface pub (CapabilityTable, Capability, ChildSlot, add_child, grant, allows, find_child, the right_* constants, the max_* bounds) -- an additive change that exposes the real table to Pool without altering behavior; confirmed the Caravan capabilities witness stays green after the edit, honoring accrete-never-break.
think composed Pool in linengrow/ (where the fold primitives kumara/receipt_core/mala_core already resolve) with a single new symlink linengrow/capabilities.rye -> ../caravan/capabilities.rye, the least-friction path to green; noted in the module doc that Pool's canonical home is a future pool/ dir, composing here for P0.
think kept P0 to the smallest real host seam per SLC/finishing: admission is a capability check (Pool asks allows(agent, resource, right) -- a name alone never admits, a real grant does), and the hosted agent's state is a verified MALA fold (never mutated in place), reusing the exact fold Neth and Sala already prove. Chose a minimal ledger agent as the first tenant, standing in honestly for the richer closed Open Ask loop (named as the P1 tenant) -- P0 proves the host seam, not a specific rich agent.
think wrote five falsifiable claims and they passed first try: a granted agent is admitted and folds to issuer 200 / holder 800; an ungranted agent is refused NotAdmitted at the door; a read-only grant is refused (the exact right is checked, not mere presence -- the capability boundary that must be sound from the first witness); two hostings agree bit-for-bit; a tampered log is refused FoldFailed so a hosted agent cannot admit a lie.
think wired P0 into parity_ch01.rish and re-ran all ten related witnesses together (Caravan + six Neth + Mantra + Sala B0 + Pool P0) -- all GREEN, no regression, confirming the additive Caravan pub edit and the new seam compose cleanly.
obs this is the design layer catching down to the build at last: the keystone the whole SLC/go-to-market strategy rested on is now a running, witnessed thing rather than a prioritized box. Pool P0 unblocks Sala B1 (live carriage) and the R-rungs -- the live broadcast the flagship experience showcases.
obs "proceed!" is a build instruction, not "send" -- so this is committed to a branch and pushed, held from main awaiting Keaton's send word, per the convention.
